    "A timedependent function expresses this evolution, and we denote the updated representation vector following an event involving node at time as.G F (v, t) → z t v z t v ∈ R d v t d ≪n t n t t Definition 5 (Dynamic graph representation learning).",
    "Given a dynamic graph evolving over time, the task of dynamic graph representation learning is to learn an efficient mapping function, where represents the timedependent low-dimensional representation of node at time.",
    "Here, and is the number of nodes in the graph at time.",
    "Models for dynamic graphsCorresponding to the different types of dynamic graphs described in Definitions 1 and 2, dynamic graph representation learning models can be divided into two main categories: discrete-time dynamic graph representation learning and continuous-time dynamic graph representation learning.",
    "The former divides the dynamic graph into multiple snapshots, which can be regarded as multiple static graphs."
